Classification.Comment: This copy number loss involves numerous protein-coding genes. Deletions that partially or completely overlap the current interval have been reported in individuals with a range of phenotypes (Fu 2021, Shimojima 2018, Rosenfeld 2010). Therefore, based on current medical literature and gene content, the 10q11.23q22.1 CNV is classified as pathogenic. References: Fu et al., BMC Pediatr. 2021 May 31;21(1):254. PMID: 34059004, Rosenfeld et al., Genet Med. 2010 Nov;12(11):694-702. PMID: 20808228, Shimojima et al., Congenit Anom (Kyoto). 2018 Jan;58(1):36-38. PMID: 28378413
